betaReductions() - Method in class nl.marcvanzee.KEProver.prover.SAKE
tries to find possible beta reductions in the current formula.

The following formulas are applicable to alpha reductions:
(0) -(p&q) & p |- -q right1-&
(1) -(p&q) & q |- -p right2-&
(2) p|q & -p |- q left1-|
(3) p|q & -q |- q left2-|
(4) p>q & p |- q left1->
(5) p>q & -q |- -p left2->
betaSubsumptions() - Method in class nl.marcvanzee.KEProver.prover.SAKE
tries to find possible beta subsumptions in the current formula.

the following formulas are applicable to beta subsumptions:
(0) p|q & p => remove p|q
(1) p|q & q => remove p|q
(2) p&p & p => remove p&p
(3) p>p & p => remove p>p
(4) p

remove p
